article.description: Will Clyburn had 22 points and nine rebounds, both game highs, to lead Utah to a 75-62 victory over TCU on Saturday.
article.headline: Will Clyburn's 22 lead Utah to victory against TCU
article.linkText: Clyburn's 22 lead Utah to victory against TCU
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas -- Will Clyburn had 22 points and nine rebounds, both game highs, to lead Utah to a 75-62 victory over TCU on Saturday. Josh Watkins scored 14 points and Shawn Glover had 11 points for the Utes (10-10, 3-3 Mountain West). Hank Thorns had 18 points, six rebounds and six assists for TCU (10-11, 1-5). Nikola Cerina scored 14 points, Garlon Green scored 12 and Ronnie Moss 10 points for the Horned Frogs. Utah shot 61.5 percent from the field (16 for 26) in the first half, but TCU managed to stay close and only trailed 38-33 at the break. The Utes finished the game at 55 percent while the Horned Frogs shot 43 percent. Glover's 3-pointer with 15:42 left gave Utah its first double-digit lead at 48-38, and the Utes kept at least an eight-point lead the rest of the way.
